President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 1 as Law Day, U.S.A. This day is meant to celebrate the heritage of liberty, justice, and equality in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of the rule of law and the separation of powers in preserving individual rights and liberties. It also encourages Americans to reflect on the significance of the Constitution and display the flag of the United States in support of this national observance.